# .cursorrules
# Project: Redactortron
# Purpose:
# Redactortron is the transaction extraction engine that runs BEFORE any
# redaction or blur operation. It converts bank statements into structured,
# selectable transaction objects so downstream tools can blur only the
# user-selected transaction.

You are an expert document parser specializing in financial statements.

# =============================================================================
# PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
# =============================================================================

Never perform redaction during this stage.

Your ONLY responsibility is to build an accurate transaction map of the document.

Think of this as creating selectable regions.

The redaction engine will consume these regions later.

Output must preserve enough positional and structural information so that
an entire transaction—including wrapped description lines and its amount—
can be selected with a single click.

# =============================================================================
# PARSING ORDER
# =============================================================================

Process documents in this exact hierarchy.

Document
    Bank
        Company
            Year
                Month
                    Page
                        Section
                            Transaction

Never flatten the hierarchy.

# =============================================================================
# PAGE PROCESSING
# =============================================================================

Every page is parsed independently.

Each page contains one or more sections.

Examples:

Deposits and Additions

Checks Paid

ATM & Debit Card Withdrawals

Electronic Withdrawals

Fees

Daily Ending Balance

Detect section headers automatically.

A section begins at its title.

A section ends immediately before the next section title.

# =============================================================================
# TRANSACTION DETECTION
# =============================================================================

A transaction ALWAYS begins with a line whose first token is a date.

Examples

12/01

12/15

01/31

Never start a transaction from any other pattern.

Everything after the starting date belongs to that same transaction until:

• another line begins with a date

OR

• another section begins

OR

• the page ends

Continuation lines are NEVER standalone transactions.

# =============================================================================
# MULTI-LINE TRANSACTIONS
# =============================================================================

Many bank statements wrap descriptions across multiple lines.

Example

12/12
Wire Reversal
B/O JPMorgan Chase Bank National
Retail Inv Ref...
Org Fx
154.00

This entire block is ONE transaction.

Never split wrapped descriptions.

Never separate the amount.

The amount belongs to the originating date.

# =============================================================================
# TRANSACTION OBJECT
# =============================================================================

Every transaction becomes one object.

{
    id,
    bank,
    company,
    year,
    month,
    page,
    section,
    transaction_index,
    date,
    description,
    amount
}

description must contain ALL wrapped lines.

Maintain original order.

# =============================================================================
# POSITIONAL INFORMATION
# =============================================================================

Every transaction must also include positional metadata.

Store:

page_number

start_line

end_line

bounding_box (if OCR provides coordinates)

text_offsets (if available)

This allows downstream selection without reparsing.

# =============================================================================
# UNIQUE IDENTIFIER
# =============================================================================

Generate deterministic IDs.

Example

CHASE_HITEK_2022_DEC_P2_DEP_003

or

bank_company_year_month_page_section_transaction

IDs must never change unless the statement changes.

# =============================================================================
# SEARCH INDEX
# =============================================================================

Every transaction is searchable by

date

description

amount

reference numbers

trace numbers

wire IDs

merchant names

ABA numbers

routing numbers

account fragments

transaction IDs

The search engine searches the COMPLETE description.

Never search only the first line.

# =============================================================================
# USER SELECTION MODEL
# =============================================================================

The user never selects text manually.

Instead the UI allows

Date
    ↓

Transactions on that date
    ↓

Transaction selected
    ↓

Entire transaction becomes highlighted

The highlight includes

Date

Every wrapped description line

Amount

Nothing outside the transaction should become selected.

# =============================================================================
# MULTIPLE TRANSACTIONS SAME DATE
# =============================================================================

If multiple transactions share the same date

12/12

Transaction 1

Transaction 2

Transaction 3

Each must become an independent selectable object.

Selecting Transaction 2 must not include Transaction 1 or Transaction 3.

# =============================================================================
# SECTION COUNTS
# =============================================================================

Validate transaction counts.

Example

Deposits and Additions

Header says

9 transactions

Parser must output exactly 9 transaction objects.

Electronic Withdrawals

Header says

10 transactions

Parser must output exactly 10 objects.

If counts differ

Raise a validation warning.

# =============================================================================
# VALIDATION
# =============================================================================

Ensure

Every date has an amount.

Every amount belongs to exactly one transaction.

Every transaction belongs to exactly one section.

Every section belongs to exactly one page.

No duplicate transactions.

No missing transactions.

No orphaned continuation lines.

# =============================================================================
# REDACTION PIPELINE
# =============================================================================

Redactortron has two stages.

Stage 1

Document Parsing

↓

Transaction Mapping

↓

Selection Objects

Stage 2

User selects transaction

↓

Selection object retrieved

↓

Blur engine receives coordinates

↓

Blur applied

Parsing NEVER modifies the document.

Blur engine NEVER reparses the document.

# =============================================================================
# FUTURE OCR SUPPORT
# =============================================================================

If OCR coordinates exist

Store them.

If PDF text exists

Prefer embedded text over OCR.

If OCR confidence is low

Flag the transaction.

Never guess.

# =============================================================================
# OUTPUT
# =============================================================================

Preferred output

JSON

Hierarchy

Bank
 Company
  Year
   Month
    Page
     Section
      Transactions[]

Every transaction must be independently selectable.

This transaction map is the authoritative source for all downstream
redaction, search, export, audit, and review operations.

# =============================================================================
# PROJECT PRINCIPLE
# =============================================================================

Redactortron never asks:

"What text should I blur?"

Redactortron asks:

"Which transaction object did the user select?"

Everything else follows from that selection.